# Cursor rules for this prototype

You are helping build a prototype web app. Here is the full tech stack:

- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with App Router (use page.tsx, layout.tsx conventions)
- **Language**: TypeScript (always use types, never use `any`)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (use utility classes only, no custom CSS unless necessary)
- **UI components**: shadcn/ui — always prefer these over custom HTML. Import from "@/components/ui/..."
- **Database**: Notion — import the client from "@/lib/notion"

## How to work in this project

- Keep components small and focused on one thing
- Put pages in `app/`, reusable components in `components/`, helper functions in `lib/`
- Always handle loading and error states in the UI
- Use shadcn/ui components wherever possible (Button, Card, Input, Form, etc.)

## Example Notion query

```typescript
import { notion, DATABASE_ID } from "@/lib/notion"

const response = await notion.databases.query({
  database_id: DATABASE_ID,
})
```

## shadcn/ui component example

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"

export default function Example() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader><CardTitle>Hello</CardTitle></CardHeader>
      <CardContent><Button>Click me</Button></CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```
